The comparison report is uploaded to JIRA see https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IOTDB-4 , here is a quick look:
<img width="416" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20263106/51451213-32101180-1d6f-11e9-9051-0f0758d7d26f.png">
@jixuan1989

I have added an IT to test float precision in iotdb/src/test/java IoTDBFloatPrecisionIT.java.
Given a float value 1.2345 and precision = 3, before flushing into disk, it is stored as 1.2345 in memory. After flushing to disk, it is stored as 1.235(after rounding) 

Node that 

